@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Flecho" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Flecho runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any arrow (the triangle-shaped icons),
this will rotate it by 45 degrees. If the corresponding amount of
arrows are pointing to a number, that number will turn to white,
otherwise it will remain black. Obviously when there is a zero, no
arrow should point to it. Continue the game until all the numbers
are in white, then the game will display how many moves you made
and a new game will start.

  You can choose the game board size, which can be from a 3 by 3
board to a 6 by 6 board. To change the board size, click on the '+'
and '-' icons located on either side under the game board, or press
on the '+' or '-' keys of the keyboard.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

